C-164  IMMUNOASSAYS: MARKETS, TECHNOLOGY,
AND PATENTS SURVEY
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>C-164  IMMUNOASSAYS: MARKETS, TECHNOLOGY,
AND PATENTS SURVEY
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>WILLIAM MURRAY</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

Immunoassays represent a large and diverse market.  The goal of this study is to
examine the state of technological development, to assess the immunoassay market
by the applications for which they are used, by the basic method used for the assay,
and to identify and forecast the impact of trends that are presently affecting the
industry.<P>



<B>REASONS FOR DOING THIS STUDY</B><P>

Immunoassay technologies have grown very rapidly in a short period of time.
Saturation has occurred in certain areas, while penetration is just beginning in others.

A great deal of similar work has been done on smaller segments of the industry.
Monoclonal antibodies, reagents for biotechnology, labels, and medical diagnostic kits
are industries that extend from or into immunoassays.  This report looks at the whole
industry and will provide critical information for decision-makers.<P>



<B>CONTRIBUTION OF THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>


<B>IMMUNOASSAYS</B><P>

This study examines the development of immunoassay technologies and the trends
affecting different methods.  It investigates applications for immunoassays and the
sizes of those markets through 1997.<P>


<B>REAGENTS</B><P>

The majority of companies that develop and market reagents also participate in the
immunoassay industry.  For companies that operate solely within the reagent
business, it presents clear, accurate assessments of the markets for their products and
key information concerning research and development efforts in the immunoassay
industry.<P>

<B>NEW INDUSTRY PARTICIPANTS AND PRESENT PLAYERS</B><P>

Of interest to both present industry participants and potential future participants,
this report identifies the market leaders in the immunoassay industry.  Market
leaders are noted and profiled.  And, through an evaluation of related U.S. patents,
technological leaders have been distinguished from the group.<P>


<B>INSTRUMENTATION AND DEVICE PRODUCERS</B><P>

While these facets of the immunoassay industry are not investigated directly, the
information presented reveals trends that influence sales of these products.  The
immunoassay markets are presented by application and by assay method.  In addition,
the degree of automation, by application, is discussed.<P>


<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The focus of this report is an assessment of immunoassay technologies and markets.
The report examines reagents: immunoassay technology development, industry
market leaders, and industry technological leaders.<P>

A complete patent analysis on immunoassays has been performed and included
because of the specialized nature of this technology.  The data-gathering portion of
this study started with a review of the pertinent U.S. patent literature.  Follow-up
calls were made to the relevant workers in the field as part of our industry contact
effort.  Market information was gathered, analyzed, and complemented by an analysis
of 727 patents that have been identified.  This study is divided into two distinct parts:<P>

(1) A market research study and industry analysis, and<P>
(2) A complete patent review, identifying involution phenomena,
 activity by assignee, technological positions, and identification of immunoassay technology ownership. In addition, there is a
 complete listing of abstracts of all patents included in the study.<P>

Market leaders and technological leaders are identified; they are not necessarily the
same companies.<P>


<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

For many years BCC has provided insightful analyses of the biotechnology industry.
As detailed in the last section of the introduction, many of the studies focus on
specific portions of the immunoassay industry.<P>

The information presented in this study comes from various sources.  These include:<P>

<UL>                        Review of U.S. patents<BR>
                        BCC business opportunity reports<BR>
                        Industry participants<BR>
                        Government data<BR>
                        Trade and relevant literature.</UL><P>

All sales figure presented, unless otherwise indicated, are presented in millions of U.S.
dollars.  Forecasts are presented in constant 1991 dollars, and the figures refer to U.S.
sales on the manufacturer level.  All forecasts are presented in table form, and critical
assumptions and influential factors are listed.<P>



<B>RELATED BCC STUDIES</B><P>

<UL><LI>             Medical Diagnostic Kits and Products
    <LI>     The Dynamic Antibody Industry, Including
                Polyclonals and Monoclonals
    <LI>     Reagents for Biotechnology: New Trends, New
                Needs
    <LI>         Reporter Tags and Linkage Agents for
                Immunoassays and Gene Probes
    <LI>         Food Testing Reagents, Including Biotechnology
    <LI>         Biotechnology for Environmental Testing </UL><P>  


