<CENTER><H2>C-198 ADVANCES AND OPPORTUNITES IN DNA-BASED TESTING
METHODS: GENE PROBES
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>BARBARA BREINDEL</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>


<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

<B>STUDY GOAL AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

This study, ADVANCES AND OPPORTUNITIES IN DNA-BASED TESTING
METHODS: GENE PROBES, focuses on providing a complete
description of the advances that have occurred in this
marketplace since BCC last examined it in 1989.  Market
opportunities are a particular focus of this report.  Gene
probe technology has been used for over 30 years, but recent
technological advances, particularly in the area of
amplification and tagging methods, have allowed for more
specificity and superior products. In addition to describing
the technology and market in detail, this report provides
data analysis and forecasts through the year 2000 on:<P>
<UL>
     <LI>market composition and dynamics
     <LI>market size
     <LI>market participants with related market share
     <LI>current and emerging technologies
     <LI>trends in utilization of various testing protocols
     <LI>impact of and trends in legal and government
regulations
     <LI>international aspects.
</UL>


<B>REASONS FOR DOING THIS STUDY</B><P>

Recent technological advances in DNA testing, including DNA
fingerprinting, clinical testing, and commercial
applications coupled with the notoriety this scientific
discipline has received in recent highly publicized trials,
make this report timely and interesting.<P>


<B>CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

This study should prove of particular value to all
participants and observers of the DNA testing industry and
the related equipment and reagents industries, as well as
researchers, laboratory and government personnel working in
the areas of genetic testing, paternity testing and
forensics.  The report defines the relevant markets with
emphasis on:<P>
<UL>
     <LI>advances in gene probe specificity
     <LI>improvements in testing procedures and equipment
     <LI>current market structure and size with forecasts
through
     <LI>2000 in constant 1996 dollars
     <LI>new marketing concepts and trends
     <LI>technological aspects and the impact of new
technologies
     <LI>on established testing procedures
     <LI>market segments
     <LI>major participants by area of participation
     <LI>impact of outside influences such as government or
legal
     <LI>decisions with identification of potential market
barriers
     <LI>government regulations and participation
     <LI>identification of niche areas offering opportunities
     <LI>corporate strategies
     <LI>international aspects of the market
     <LI>analogous markets.
</UL>





<B>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

The DNA testing market in its entirety is examined in this
report with particular emphasis on those areas that are
experiencing innovative technological development.
Companies serving this marketplace are examined to define
which will prove to be market leaders through the year 2000.<P>

DNA testing is segmented into many disciplines including
clinical diagnosis, forensic applications, research,
industrial applications, food testing, agricultural,
anthropological and reference laboratory uses.  This report
focuses on all of these areas, as well as emerging
applications and analogous markets.<P>


<B>METHODOLOGY</B><P>

The methodologies employed in this study include use of both
primary interviews with industry personnel and analysis of
secondary data.  Among the primary data sources are
scientists and technologists performing forensic
examinations, company personnel, government and regulatory
representatives, industry observers, and industry
professional organizations.<P>

Growth forecasts are made in constant 1996 dollars based on
the manufacturers' (wholesale) price level unless otherwise
noted.<P>

All data collected was reviewed by BCC's specialists in the
laboratory testing industry and all findings and projections
were confirmed with numerous industry sources.<P>

<B>INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

Data sources for this report include information obtained
from interviews with various market participants,
scientists, government personnel, trade association members,
and observers.  BCC's extensive library also served as a
data source as did corporate and industry trade association
publications and industry data banks.<P>



<B>RELATED BCC WORK CREDENTIALS</B><P>

The BCC project director of this report holds both medical
technology and advanced marketing degrees.  Further
supporting the analyst's knowledge in this area is extensive
experience in the pharmaceutical industry, the medical
device industry, and in other high technology markets.  The
most recent studies published by this analyst are a study of
changes in the drug industry including changing markets and
marketing techniques, changing strategies, and the changing
structure.  Other recent studies include an examination of
the emerging opportunities in the U.S. health care delivery
system in the year 2000, an examination of the medical
diagnostic kits and products market, and a report on the
U.S. blood industry.  Other reports issued by this analyst
are reports on trends in noninvasive and minimally invasive
medical devices, microorganism testing systems, gene probe
markets, bioengineered protein drugs, new drug delivery
systems, medical diagnostic equipment, biocompatible
materials, and the laser industry.<P>

Published BCC reports related to the present topic include:<P>

<UL>
     <LI>C-155  -    INFORMATION AND DATA HANDLING DEVELOPMENTS
                   IN  MEDICINE  HIGHLIGHTING  OPPORTUNITIES
       FOR:
                 HARDWARE, SOFTWARE AND SERVICES
     
     <LI>C-181   -    THE CHANGING DRUG INDUSTRY: CHANGING
       MARKETS
                 AND MARKETING TECHNIQUES, CHANGING
                 STRATEGIES, CHANGING STRUCTURE

     <LI>C-170  -    MARKETS FOR VACCINES AND DRUGS FOR AIDS
       AND
                 AIDS-ASSOCIATED MEDICAL CONDITIONS
     
     <LI>C-045N -    MEDICAL DIAGNOSTIC KITS AND PRODUCTS
     
