<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
C-148R: THE DYNAMIC IMAGING CHEMICALS MARKET
IN MICROELECTRONICS
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>C-148R: THE DYNAMIC IMAGING CHEMICALS MARKET
IN MICROELECTRONICS
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>Dirk Muyskens</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>


This report describes the markets and technology for imaging and associated chemicals in the production of integrated circuits and printed circuit boards.  These products consist of photoresists, developers, strippers, etchants and related materials. Photoresists are defined as organic coatings activated by light patterns so that those precise, thin lines can be formed on the coated surface.<P> 

<B>STUDY GOALS AND OBJECTIVES</B><P>

The object of this study is to describe the composition of photoresists and 
how they are applied and developed, to provide information on the market size 
and producers of these coatings, and to forecast technological developments 
and market growth.<P> 


<b>REASONS FOR DOING THE STUDY</B><P>

This study is an in-depth examination of the photoresist industry.  Electronic 
chemicals and materials are the fundamental technology at the heart of today's 
electronic products. Therefore, developments in photoresist technology are at 
the center of the thrust to pack more and more capability in integrated 
circuits and printed circuit boards.  Line widths are the critical factor and 
the full thrust of research and development in photoresists is to keep 
reducing these line widths.<P> 

<b>CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE STUDY AND FOR WHOM</B><P>

This study is of value to the following decision makers who need strategic information on the electronic chemicals industry and its markets:<P> 

<UL>    Electronic materials suppliers<BR>
    Suppliers of resins and substrates<BR>
    Suppliers of semiconductors and devices<BR>
    Suppliers of printed circuit boards<BR>
    Electronic and electrical equipment manufacturers<BR>
    Merge, acquisition and investment executives</UL><P>

<b>SCOPE AND FORMAT</B><P>

This BCC analytical tool covers the new technologies in terms of materials, 
processes and applications.  The chapters reveal the emerging technologies and 
then make analytical market and industry forecasts that identify paths to new 
and profitable business opportunities.  An extensive directory of suppliers 
provides a one-stop source for microelectronic material needs.<P> 


<b>METHODOLOGY AND INFORMATION SOURCES</B><P>

Data are based on a thorough review of electronic materials technology based on a systematic review of developments through telephone and in-person reviews and an extensive data base of technical and marketing sources.<P> 

Additional data for this document were obtained from a review of technical papers and from discussions and in-depth interviews with a representative sample of vendors, end-users and trade associations.<P> 

<b>RELATED BCC RESEARCH CREDENTIALS</B><P>

BCC has published many reports in the electronics and chemicals areas.  The 
more recent include:<P> 

<UL>     C-152-R--Ultrapure Chemicals and Water for the
               Semiconductive Industry<P>
     C-192--Alternative Technologies to Regulated Cleaning
               Solvents:  A Growing Industry<P>
     C-137R--Environmentally Acceptable Soldering and Cleanup
               Materials and Systems in Electronics<P>
     G-152--PCMCIA Technology:  Impressive Growth Through 2000,
               Uncertainty Beyond<P>
     G067X--Printed Circuit Boards:  Markets and Opportunities<P>
     GB-138R--Multichip Packaging and Base Chip Systems</UL><P>


