<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>
G-131R  WIRELESS COMMUNICATIONS WITH 1993 UPDATE ADDENDUM
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="bccLogoSmall.gif" ALT="LOGO">
<CENTER><H2>G-131R  WIRELESS COMMUNICATIONS WITH 1993 UPDATE ADDENDUM
</H2>

<HR><P>

<I>VTOM RUSH</I><BR>
PROJECT ANALYST
<P>

<H3><I>ADDENDUM INTRODUCTION</I></H3>
</CENTER>

Rather than rewriting the entire report entitled "Wireless
Communications" issued just over twenty months ago, BCC has chosen
to update that report with this addendum.  The sections of the
original report that deal with background, technology, applications
and economics have had little or no change in the intervening
months.  Therefore, this addendum will deal mainly with the
forecasts and outlook for wireless communications, updating and/or
replacing the original, and commenting on the factors that have
changed since the original forecasts were produced.<P>

Since this is an addendum of change, the original report in its
entirety remains valid, and is the basis for all comment in this
latest update.  In particular, the driving forces, issues, and
generally optimistic growth outlook as expressed in conclusions
noted in the Summary of the original report remain valid.  What has
changed is that wireless is seen as even more pervasive now than
just two years ago, even with our optimistic (and realistic taken
in hindsight) forecasts of acceptance.  This addendum is organized
with the same sub-headings within the Forecast and Outlook section
as used in the original report -- which is to say, the addendum is
organized by type of wireless application and equipment, such as
cellular, VSAT, LANs, etc.<P>



